						               													<description>A game to challenge your luck and your memory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Search for the hidden monsters, but only the ones of the color that matches the dice!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective of the game is to gather the largest number of cards, whoever gets the highest number will be the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each one in his turn, must roll the dice and according to the color that comes out, it is the indicated monster to look for in the grid of cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A card is turned over, if it contains a monster of the color of the die, you can take the card and end the turn, or you can choose to continue play and turn over another card, as long as it contains the monster, you can continue, but do not force a lot of luck, that it can fail and if you turn over a monster of another color, you will not take anything and all the cards are turned over again. To use memory and remember where each monster is, so in your turn you take more cards!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can always keep turning over cards, but be careful not to push your luck! Or you won't get anything. If you turn one over and it does not have a monster of the color of the dice, the hand is over, the cards are turned over again, but take advantage and test your memory to remember where they are!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The cards in the grid are filled up until there are none left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3 rounds are played and whoever has the most cards wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If there is a tie, the monsters per card are counted and the tie is broken.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
